<h2 id=3D"id-07.SD:AccountGrouping-RAID-Risk,Assumptions,IssuesandDependenc=
ies">RAID - Risk, Assumptions, Issues and Dependencies</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-07.SD:AccountGrouping-Constraints&amp;Dependencies">Constraint=
s &amp; Dependencies</h3>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup class=3D"">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 364.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 372.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 480.0px;">
<col class=3D"" style=3D"width: 184.0px;">
</colgroup>
<tbody class=3D"">
<tr class=3D"">
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Ref #</st=
rong></p><p>[C-###, D-###]</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Considera=
tions Type</strong></p><p>[Constraints, Dependencies]</p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Descripti=
on</strong></p></th>
<th style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTh"><p><strong>Date</str=
ong></p></th>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C1</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>Addition of query=
 param in existing endpoint GET /arrangements&nbsp;</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Addition of optional=
 query param in the existing endpoint.</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr class=3D"">
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C2</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The account group=
s/account list will not be a sorted list.</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>PDP will not do s=
orting in account groups response &amp; in fetching the list of accounts.</=
p><p><span style=3D"color: rgb(23,43,77);">Channels will do the sorting&nbs=
p; by account name in ascending alphabetical order.</span></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C3</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>The assumption is=
 sorting or account listing will be done at CAP API layer.(<strong>TBC</str=
ong>)</p>
<ul>
<li>we pass all account Ids (eg: 1000) as-is from ent lib to CAP. CAP sorts=
 and return 1st 500 (<strong>TBC</strong>)</li>
</ul><p><br></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C4</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>On click of refre=
sh icon account groups will not get refreshed.</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C5</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span data-teams=
=3D"true">PDP server side library will give us the account ids both closed =
&amp; active accounts.</span></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C6</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>By default accoun=
t listing table&nbsp; should have all the active accounts.</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">A user can anytime g=
o in and check for closed accounts if they want see closed account listing =
also.</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C7</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span data-teams=
=3D"true">We can get the list of accounts even though we got an error when =
loading the list of account groups.</span></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">This can happen when=
 there is an error loading account groups but accounts were loaded successf=
ully.</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C8</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span data-teams=
=3D"true">On page load default behaviour is </span></p>
<ol>
<li><span data-teams=3D"true">All accounts option is selected by default in=
 typeahead component.</span></li>
<li><span data-teams=3D"true">"Include all closed accounts" options should =
be unchecked, but a user can go anytime and tick this selection so as to ge=
t the closed accounts also.</span></li>
</ol></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd">Once the user ticks =
the Include closed accounts options then AG Grid should have both closed an=
d active account status.</td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>C9</p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><p><span data-teams=
=3D"true">"All Accounts" will not come as a response&nbsp; from account gro=
ups call, consider it as a hard coded value and when this option is selecte=
d current flow to fetch the list of accounts will take place and the PDP re=
sponse will not have any ScopeId and Scope Name associated with All Account=
s.</span></p></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
<td style=3D"text-align: left;" class=3D"confluenceTd"><br></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"id-07.SD:AccountGrouping-KeyDecisions"><span>Key Decisions</span>=
</h2>
<p><span>The Galaxy Accounts MFE EXP API will have a new endpoints:</span><=
/p>
<ol>
<li>To fetch the account Groups -GET- /accountGroups</li>
<li>Addition of query param in existing endpoint GET /arrangements.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>&nbsp;The above applies to statements page also.</strong></p>
<h2 id=3D"id-07.SD:AccountGrouping-UserStoryTraceability"><span>User Story =
Traceability</span></h2>
<p><br></p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"relative-table wrapped confluenceTable" style=3D"width: 563=
.0px;">
<colgroup class=3D"">
