<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><br></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><strong>b. Change in the existing API GET /a=
rrangements:-</strong></p>
<ol>
<li style=3D"text-align: left;">Add an optional query parameter i.e <strong=
>groupId as a query param to the existing endpoint.- </strong>This query pa=
ram will only be added once we have<strong> the success response from GET /=
accountGroups API response otherwise not.</strong></li>
<li style=3D"text-align: left;">This groupId is received as a response from=
 the GET /accountGroups API response.</li>
<li style=3D"text-align: left;">When the EXPAPI calls PDP Server side libra=
ry with groupId as a query param then PDP will return the account list asso=
ciated with the selected group.</li>
<li style=3D"text-align: left;">Once we have the account list then the flow=
 will continue as is EXP=E2=86=92 will call=E2=86=92 CAP, to fetch the acco=
unt listing.</li>
<li style=3D"text-align: left;">In UI the account listing should be display=
ed in ascending order based on account number.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><br></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><strong>Note</strong>:-</p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;">Here are some of the validations which needs=
 to be taken care of while creating EXP API swagger patterns- <a href=3D"/d=
isplay/ARTC/Neptune+Field+Validations">Neptune Field Validations</a></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: left;"><br></p>
